posts.name: ScottRandallWay
posts.cooked:
I am converting our robot from labview to java.  I am trying to create a doublesolenoid, but I just keep getting ‘ CAN : message not found’ errors.  I know the wiring is fine because it all works with labview.  I am using the same ports they are using with labview.  They are plugged into a rev robotics pnuematics hub.  The hub is tied into the CAN .  I tried creating a pnuematichub, but that also throws the same not found message.  What am I missing here?

solenoid = new DoubleSolenoid( PneumaticsModuleType.REVPH, PnuematicChannels.ALGAE_GRABBER_FORWARD, PnuematicChannels.ALGAE_GRABBER_REVERSE);

posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked: You say the wiring is fine, but just to confirm, if you connect to the REV PH via USB-C and open the REV Hardware Client, do you see the whole bus? Specifically can you see the RoboRio?

posts.name: SLAB-Mr.Thomas
posts.cooked: You didn’t post your complete code; you can take a look at our complete code that works. Look at the Pneumatics.java and Shifter.java in Subsystems for the compressor, Rev hub, and double solenoid.

posts.name: Julius
posts.cooked: I’m sure this isn’t the case but our T-shirt cannon was built very strangely to where our solenoids were hooked up to the DIO ports… try to create a new DigitalOutput(make sure it’s output not input) then treat it like a Boolean so set it to true or false

posts.name: ScottRandallWay
posts.cooked: My code is consistent with the pneumatics and shifter subsystems.  If I load the rev hardware client it does not see the pneumatics hub.  I thought if I loaded it I could see the correct module for it, but it is not there.  I also do not see it in the phoenix tuner.  I know it works with the labview code so I know the wiring is sound.

when you connect the usb-c from the computer to the pneumatics hub the rev software client cant see the pnumatics hub? if the rev software cliant cant see the pneumatics hub there might be an issue with the hub.

posts.name: ScottRandallWay
posts.cooked: but if I push the labview code to the robot it works.

posts.name: ScottRandallWay
posts.cooked: okay I missed the usb c port directly on the pnuematics hub.  I can see it now.  let’s see if I can get what I need from it.

posts.name: ScottRandallWay
posts.cooked: Hey that did the trick.  Using the rev hardware client I could see the correct module was 41.  When I created the pneumatics hub with the module 41 everything worked.  I used the enablableCompressorDigital and makeDoubleSolenoid methods on the hub object to get everything to work from there.  Rock on!
